<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Warriors should generate the most damage of any class. The only class that should come close are monks, and tied at a distant third are paladins and shadowknights. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Let me get this straight.  Warriors should have the most hp, most ac and deal out the most damage of any class?  Why would anyone play any class but this Superman class.  If warriors dealt more damage than rogues or monks, why would anyone choose to play either class?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I have very average gear yet had no trouble holding aggro with 31% haste, 44 delay weapon ( no taunting type proc ) tanking UNSLOWED mobs in a group of 65s the other day including a rogue and monk. Granted the other mellees were skilled at funnelling aggro to me which makes a bigger difference than any gear, but I agree that warriors need some other 'trick' for the sub 90 AA'd who can't devote xp to offensive gear. In the meantime just plow away AA til you become a QUINTUPLE attack ( eat your heart out monks =P ) DPS machine.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I was the monk in question.  I don't want to burst your bubble as you are a fine warrior but I was chain-feigning while we were fighting.  I am pretty sure Rodric was evading.  If either of us had wanted to get aggro, it wouldn't have been difficult as there is a significant dps disparity.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Warrior dps is quite a bit lower than shadowknight dps assuming equal gear. Paladin dps can situationally, i.e lots of undead, blow both away. Generally the dps curve looks like SKs &gt; warriors &gt; paladins.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I am not sure what you are smoking but pass me some of that.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Shadowknights have terrible dps--they are near the bottom of all classes.  I outdamage comparably geared shadowknights by a huge margin.  Comparably geared warriors will also outdamage shadowknights.<br>
<br>
Paladins?  They might have the lowest dps of any class, save for clerics.  I have grouped with paladins with more expensive gear than I have and outdamage them routinely by a healthy margin.  In a typical grind group, a comparably geared warrior (especially if he/she is not tanking) will outdamage a paladin or shadowknight.<br>
<br>
--Trakon<br>
<br>
/agree Jebbar<br>
