 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vicairedelestacia>Vicaire Delestacia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/03 1:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4984.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior ideas</span><hr size=1> If you are speaking pure melee damage then yes warriors can outdamage SK and paladins.  With spells though SKs outdamage warriors by quite a bit.  With undead procs, paladins outdamage warriors by a large margin on undead mobs.  Its as easy as parsing. Paladins fall behind warriors in general dps since they don't have any spells to augment thier general damage.  SKs have dots, nukes, and innate procs that give them a decent advantage over warriors.  Given equal gear and levels/AA, SKs will outdamage warriors on almost all mobs in the game and of course depending on the length and type of battle, can blow them away completely in some situations.  For sustained dps which includes melee and spell damage, warriors just can't beat SKs.<br>
<br>
<br>
This is a large part of the warrior problem right now. Defensive seems to be pretty much the only advantage warriors have on knights.  The hp advantage of warriors has diminished greatly in the last two expansions and knight dps is either greater or situationally much greater.  This leaves warriors who are not in the high end game where defensive is absolutely required feeling very useless. Why have a warrior when a knight can tank almost as well and can have instant aggro lock? Why take a warrior who can only tank when you can have a knight that brings so much more to the table?<br>
<br>
Vicaire Delestacia<br>
